docs.abstract: The president found friendly airwaves on WABC-AM’s “Bernie & Sid in the Morning,” where he said he would shun the gala for the second straight year.

docs.lead_paragraph: Donny from D.C., you’re on the air.

headline.main: Trump to Skip Correspondents’ Dinner. But Talk Radio? He’s In.
headline.print_headline: Trump Will Skip the Correspondents’ Dinner. But Talk Radio? He’s In.

docs.abstract: Social media wits saw an “It Girl” who attained power through deference. Reporters considered her a straight shooter with direct access to the president.
docs.snippet: Social media wits saw an “It Girl” who attained power through deference. Reporters considered her a straight shooter with direct access to the president.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Hope Hicks walked into President Trump’s private study on Wednesday to inform him that she planned to leave the White House — concluding a can’t-make-it-up run in which Ms. Hicks, a woman with zero political experience three years ago, became the closest aide to the most powerful man in the world — the president responded like a father whose daughter had outgrown the nest.

headline.main: Trump Is ‘Losing a Limb’ With the Departure of Hope Hicks
headline.print_headline: Disenchantment for Aide Grew With the Spotlight

docs.abstract: Congress created a fix-it fund for borrowers in the public service loan forgiveness plan. Many categories of educators, lawyers and others are ineligible.
docs.snippet: Congress created a fix-it fund for borrowers in the public service loan forgiveness plan. Many categories of educators, lawyers and others are ineligible.
docs.lead_paragraph: Two weeks ago, Congress created a $350 million pot of money to help teachers, firefighters and others in public service who thought they were enrolled in a program that would forgive their student loans after 10 years of payments. Many of them were not getting credit for their loan payments after all.

headline.main: A $350 Million Fund Helps Many Public Servants. Meet the Ones Left Out.
headline.print_headline: A Fix-It Fund  That Isn’t a Fix For All Debtors

docs.abstract: The Silicon Valley digital payments company reached a deal for iZettle, which is Europe’s answer to the mobile payments company Square.
